headline: What Qualcomm’s New Arm Chip Upgrade Means for Shareholders in 2025
summary: If you’re holding QUALCOMM stock, or thinking about making your next move, let’s talk about what’s really going on under the hood. After all, QUALCOMM has been anything but quiet lately. The stock is up 3.3% over the last month, standing at $165.46 after the most recent close. While it has only moved -0.6% over both the past week and the past year, its three-year performance tells a more energizing story: up 63.2%, and a solid 41.8% gain over five years. Not too shabby for a tech giant...
